http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Fire-in-village-destroys-15-houses/article13998965.ece

A major fire accident caused tension among villagers of Antakapalli, Rajam mandal of Srikakulam district on Wednesday early hours.According to police, electric short circuit triggered fire and destroyed 15 houses.The villagers remained panic-stricken following the blast of five cylinders. Flames spread to other parts destroying property worth Rs. 30 lakh. No one was injured in the incident. However the fire accident took away the happiness of Sankranti festival.The district administration revenue, police teams immediately to help victims. Srikakulam collector P. Lakshmi Narasimham n Srikakulam SP AS Khan inquired about the incident. Rajam MLA Kambala Jogulu visited the spot n urged official to release compensation n essential commodities. He interacted with villagers and asked about the incident.